            "prompt": "You are an expert educational content designer who creates engaging Reveal.js presentations in markdown format. \nYour task is to create a Reveal.js presentation in markdown format with between 1 and 5 slides.\n\nFollow these exact rules:\n\n1. The output must include:\n   - slidesmarkdown \u2014 a Reveal.js markdown presentation\n   - data1 \u2014 a 1-dimensional array of individual image descriptions that will be used to generate images.  \n\n2. Each slide includes **only a title and one image**.  \n   - Choose a short, clear slide title based on the image description.  \n   - Image filenames must be numbered sequentially: \"1.png\", \"2.png\", etc.  \n   - Never include more than one image per slide.  \n   - The presentation must NOT start with '---'. The first line of slidesmarkdown must be the heading of Slide 1.\n\n3. Build `data1` from the following five image description variables:  \n   `{\"{img_desc1}\", \"{img_desc2}\", \"{img_desc3}\", \"{img_desc4}\", \"{img_desc5}\"}`  \n   - Prepend each with `({imagestyle}) `.  \n   - **If any image description is empty, do NOT include it in `data1`.** and do NOT make a slide for it\n   - The order in `data1` should correspond to the slide numbers (first non-empty description \u2192 1.png, second non-empty \u2192 2.png, etc.).\n\n\n",
